Arcelormittal South Africa Shares Fall After Furnace Fails

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-08-10T08:10:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/arcelormittal-south-africa-shares-fall-in-johannesburg-after-furnace-fails.html
ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL) 
shares fell as much as 4.1 percent in Johannesburg trading after
the company said a blast furnace in Newcastle,  South Africa 
failed.  The stock traded 2.8 percent down at 59.20 rand as of 10:09
a.m. Johannesburg time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  